00:04:27.060 --> 00:04:30.450
So let's just do a
little bit of notation.

00:04:30.450 --> 00:04:32.940
I actually looked it up on
Wikipedia and they had one

00:04:32.940 --> 00:04:34.320
definition-- maybe it
wasn't Wikipedia, it was

00:04:34.320 --> 00:04:36.290
maybe another website.

00:04:36.290 --> 00:04:38.210
And actually, I think you
do see this definition of

00:04:38.210 --> 00:04:41.490
lot where they say the
probability-- sometimes it's

00:04:41.490 --> 00:04:44.090
written as probability of a.

00:04:44.090 --> 00:04:46.430
Sometimes it's just
written as P of a.

00:04:46.430 --> 00:04:54.480
So the probability of a
occurring is equal to the

00:04:54.480 --> 00:05:06.810
events in which a is true
over total number of events.

00:05:06.810 --> 00:05:10.130
And this, for the most part,
can be a good definition, but

00:05:10.130 --> 00:05:11.630
I'll show you one place where
I think it's a little

00:05:11.630 --> 00:05:13.450
bit more squirmy.

00:05:13.450 --> 00:05:17.270
So if I told you that I'm
going to flip a coin and--

00:05:17.270 --> 00:05:17.990
actually, even better.

00:05:17.990 --> 00:05:19.930
Let's say, let's roll a dice.

00:05:19.930 --> 00:05:23.640
And let's say I say the
probability-- I'm going

00:05:23.640 --> 00:05:25.730
straight to more
difficult things.

00:05:25.730 --> 00:05:30.670
So say the probability
of an even number.

00:05:30.670 --> 00:05:33.040
Well, let's use this
definition that they gave.

00:05:33.040 --> 00:05:35.630
Well, what's the probability
that this event is true?

00:05:35.630 --> 00:05:37.290
Well, let's see, what are all
the numbers I could get?

00:05:37.290 --> 00:05:40.110
I could get a 1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6.

00:05:40.110 --> 00:05:44.030
This is just a normal die, it's
not one of those Dungeons

00:05:44.030 --> 00:05:45.800
and Dragon's dice.

00:05:45.800 --> 00:05:49.850
So what are the number of
events where we get an even

00:05:49.850 --> 00:05:52.640
number, where this is
true, where even is true?

00:05:52.640 --> 00:05:54.390
Let's see.

00:05:54.390 --> 00:05:56.490
2, 4, 6.

00:05:56.490 --> 00:06:00.250
Those are all the situations
where we get even as true.

00:06:00.250 --> 00:06:03.070
So there are 3 where
even is true.

00:06:03.070 --> 00:06:05.110
And then, what is the
total number of events?

00:06:05.110 --> 00:06:07.860
Well, we could get 1 of 6
numbers, so there are 6 total.

00:06:07.860 --> 00:06:09.440
And that equals 1/2.

00:06:09.440 --> 00:06:11.300
And that also
equals 50%, right?

00:06:11.300 --> 00:06:14.770
We know how to convert
fractions to percentages.

00:06:14.770 --> 00:06:17.970
And this is right, this
is completely right.

00:06:17.970 --> 00:06:21.700
But the only time where you can
really apply this and most of

00:06:21.700 --> 00:06:24.980
what you'll do in school and
things you can apply this, but

00:06:24.980 --> 00:06:27.760
this assumes that all of the
events are equally

00:06:27.760 --> 00:06:29.640
likely to occur.

00:06:29.640 --> 00:06:33.400
You could have had a dice or
a die-- I forgot how to say

00:06:33.400 --> 00:06:36.280
the plural or the singular.

00:06:36.280 --> 00:06:40.410
You could have that situation
where maybe the six-sided is

00:06:40.410 --> 00:06:41.340
weighted a little bit more.

00:06:41.340 --> 00:06:43.220
You know, someone's handed
it down so it's more likely

00:06:43.220 --> 00:06:44.340
to have a 3 or something.

00:06:44.340 --> 00:06:47.780
And in that case, you wouldn't
be able to use this definition.

00:06:47.780 --> 00:06:49.520
So I'm going to modify
this definition, although

00:06:49.520 --> 00:06:51.830
I don't know if it's
traditionally modified.

00:06:51.830 --> 00:06:56.620
This is one possible, events
in which a is true divided

00:06:56.620 --> 00:07:00.210
by-- well, let's say,
equally probable.

00:07:00.210 --> 00:07:06.090
Equally probable events in
which a is true divided by

00:07:06.090 --> 00:07:11.580
equally probable total events.

00:07:11.580 --> 00:07:15.300
So in order for this to hold
true each of these six

00:07:15.300 --> 00:07:18.260
circumstances have to have
exact equal chance

00:07:18.260 --> 00:07:19.110
of occurring.

00:07:19.110 --> 00:07:21.370
And we're going to do maybe
in this video, actually

00:07:21.370 --> 00:07:23.250
probably not in this, I
