or we'll have a set of

00:07:32.160 --> 00:07:35.180
circumstances where all of--
each of the total number events

00:07:35.180 --> 00:07:36.410
they're not equally probable.

00:07:36.410 --> 00:07:37.790
So that's why I want you
become a little bit

00:07:37.790 --> 00:07:41.900
weary of this situation.

00:07:41.900 --> 00:07:45.800
So with that said, let's do a
couple of probability problems

00:07:45.800 --> 00:07:49.520
that maybe give you a little
bit more intuition for--

00:07:49.520 --> 00:07:52.460
whoops-- for what's going on
here in the world

00:07:52.460 --> 00:07:54.900
of probability.

00:07:54.900 --> 00:07:57.070
So if I'm flipping a dice and
I said, well, what's the

00:07:57.070 --> 00:07:59.620
probability of heads?

00:07:59.620 --> 00:08:00.300
That's pretty easy.

00:08:00.300 --> 00:08:02.080
We could use that definition
and it's a completely

00:08:02.080 --> 00:08:03.560
fair dice.

00:08:03.560 --> 00:08:06.330
We could use that definition
and say, well, what are the

00:08:06.330 --> 00:08:07.800
total number of events where
I could get heads

00:08:07.800 --> 00:08:08.680
or tails, right?

00:08:08.680 --> 00:08:10.190
So there's 2 total events.

00:08:10.190 --> 00:08:11.490
And the probability the
getting heads, that's

00:08:11.490 --> 00:08:12.105
one of the events.

00:08:12.105 --> 00:08:14.210
So there's a 1/2 probability.

00:08:14.210 --> 00:08:16.260
The way I like to think of it
so we don't have to use that

00:08:16.260 --> 00:08:21.970
previous definition is, if I
were to conduct this experiment

00:08:21.970 --> 00:08:26.260
a hundred times, what
percentage of those times am

00:08:26.260 --> 00:08:28.410
I likely to get heads?

00:08:28.410 --> 00:08:31.340
And then I would say, well,
there's 50% of the time

00:08:31.340 --> 00:08:32.290
I would get heads.

00:08:32.290 --> 00:08:35.020
And the reason why, you know, I
could make a symmetry argument

00:08:35.020 --> 00:08:38.650
that it's just as likely to go
on heads as it is to tails.

00:08:38.650 --> 00:08:41.330
There's no reason why I
would expect 51 heads or

00:08:41.330 --> 00:08:43.224
49 nine tails, although
that could happen.

00:08:43.224 --> 00:08:44.720
But there's no reason
I could expect it.

00:08:44.720 --> 00:08:46.580
Heads and tails are
equally likely.

00:08:46.580 --> 00:08:49.670
They're just different words
for different sides of a

00:08:49.670 --> 00:08:51.970
coin that's equally likely
to fall on either side.

00:08:51.970 --> 00:08:58.050
Anyway, let's say I'm going
to now flip a coin twice.

00:08:58.050 --> 00:08:58.790
And it's the same coin.

00:08:58.790 --> 00:09:00.040
So I'm going to flip it, and
then I'm going to pick it up,

00:09:00.040 --> 00:09:01.050
and I'm going to flip it again.

00:09:01.050 --> 00:09:04.960
And so what's the probability
that I get-- I'll

00:09:04.960 --> 00:09:06.970
call it heads, heads.

00:09:06.970 --> 00:09:09.950
So that's the probability that
I get heads on the first flip

00:09:09.950 --> 00:09:12.550
and then heads on
the second flip.

00:09:12.550 --> 00:09:13.870
Well, look at it this way.

00:09:13.870 --> 00:09:18.010
If on the first flip we already
know that we have a 5% chance

00:09:18.010 --> 00:09:21.210
or 1/2 chance on the
first flip, right?

00:09:21.210 --> 00:09:25.300
So let's think of it of the
frequentist philosophy.

00:09:25.300 --> 00:09:29.840
So if I were to do this a
hundred times, 50 of the

00:09:29.840 --> 00:09:31.690
times I would get heads.

00:09:31.690 --> 00:09:33.340
Let's call that on
the first flip.

00:09:33.340 --> 00:09:35.790
Then of course, 50 of the
times I would get tails

00:09:35.790 --> 00:09:37.970
on the first flip, right?

00:09:37.970 --> 00:09:40.010
Now we're at this state of the
universe and now we do the

00:09:40.010 --> 00:09:42.480
experiment over again.

00:09:42.480 --> 00:09:49.880
So of these 50 times, what
percentage of the times is

00:09:49.880 --> 00:09:54.320
the next flip going
to be heads again?

00:09:54.320 --> 00:09:57.850
Well, we could say it's going
to be another 50% chance, or

00:09:57.850 --> 00:10:01.780
you could say, well, in 50
tries the first one was heads,

00:10:01.780 --> 00:10:06.510
and then of those 50, 50%
are going to be heads again.

00:10:06.510 --> 00:10:08.270
So we get 25%.

00:10:08.270 --> 00:10:10.080
I just multiplied
these two numbers.

00:10:10.080 --> 00:10:13.910
And of course, to get heads and
then tails would be 25% chance.

00:10:13.910 --> 00:10:18.230
Heads Heads, heads tails,
and then this is tails

00:10:18.230 --> 00:10:20.546
heads, tails heads.

